text.section:
The Board of Trustees of the Community College for Baltimore County may award a procurement contract on the basis of noncompetitive negotiation:
For unsolicited offers that:
Are in writing;
Are sufficiently detailed to allow a judgment regarding the potential utility of the offer;
Are unique or innovative;
Demonstrate the proprietary character of the offering warranting consideration of the use of competitive negotiation;
May be subject to testing under terms and conditions specified by the Director of Purchasing; and
Cannot be procured through competitive methodologies;
For the procurement of goods or services related to instruction or curriculum development;
For the procurement of services related to private fund-raising activities; or
Under other circumstances when the Director of Purchasing determines that noncompetitive negotiation is in the best interests of the College and the State.
